      </p>

     </div>
     <div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA10d079n1-ptr" id="PJA10d079n1">1</a>
      
   <p><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> is referring to Thomas Digges letter of <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-10-02-0055" class="document">29 Aug.</a> (and <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-10-02-0055&amp;expandNote=PJA10d066n5#PJA10d066n5" class="document">note 5</a>, above). <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> had acknowledged that letter and one of <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-10-02-0049" class="document">25 Aug.</a> (above) in a brief note dated <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-10-03-0001-0118" class="document">4 Sept.</a> (<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ letterbook copy (Letterbook copies are normally unsigned, but any such copy is assumed to be in the hand of the person responsible for the text unless it is otherwise described.) ]">LbC</abbr>, <span class="ref-terms">Adams Papers</span>).</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA10d079n2-ptr" id="PJA10d079n2">2</a>
      
